# Liahona.AI Sources

## Source Hierarchy

Canonical sources have the highest grounding authority.

Interpretive systems exist to symbolically reflect, organize, and orient around those sources.

Live/current sources provide temporal awareness but are not canonical.

## Canonical Sources

Examples:
- Bible
- Book of Mormon
- Doctrine and Covenants
- Pearl of Great Price
- Gospel Library
- Guide to the Scriptures
- ChurchOfJesusChrist.org

Canonical sources should remain:
- outward-facing
- clearly sourced
- non-modified
- authoritative outside the system

Liahona.AI is not itself the authority.
It points outward toward grounding sources.

## Interpretive Sources

Interpretive systems may include:
- symbolic architecture
- continuity philosophy
- artifact metaphors
- experiential design
- reflective systems
- orientation models

Interpretive systems are:
- human-built
- non-canonical
- symbolic
- experiential

## Live Sources

Live/current-event information should:
- remain clearly time-bound
- preserve uncertainty when necessary
- avoid overstating confidence
- prefer trustworthy external sources

## Source Hygiene

Never blur:
- canon
- interpretation
- speculation
- runtime behavior
- live information

Maintain epistemic clarity across time.